post_text:
Hello Mustangs!

As the 2nd Six-Weeks is approaching, it is time once again to make a selection. All students have the option to participate full-time in our Online Home Based Learning, or Face to Face On-Campus Instruction. All students will have the option each 6 weeks to change their opt-in choice.

You do NOT have to complete the form if you wish for your child to remain in their current learning option.

Please visit this link to complete: http://bit.ly/2nd6weeksForm

Forms must be completed by September 18, 2020

post_text:
Our Maintenance Crew has been going above and beyond to ensure our facilities are properly sanitized as we get ready to return to face to face on Tuesday, September 8th! Yesterday morning, AR Extreme representatives came out to properly train and educate our maintenance staff on how to use this product safely in order to effectively sanitize all areas.

Extreme Antimicrobial is used by many districts around Texas and beyond and has rave reviews! It kills germs and bacteria for 72 hours (even when surfaces are touched by students, teachers, etc.)!!

Thank you Maintenance Department for ALL you do for our District!!

post_text: After completing the investigation and contact tracing among our football players, IISD Administrators and Coaching Staff have declared the situation as isolated. The player that received the positive results and those that were in direct contact with him, will remain in self-isolation for the duration of the quarantine period outlined in the UIL guidelines. Following the direction of TEA/UIL/CDC, we have made the decision to continue the Junior High and High School football programs effective Thursday, August 20, 2020, with practices resuming as originally scheduled. We remain committed to the safety of our players and staff and will continue to monitor future situations. Thank you for your understanding and support and we will be sure to provide as much information as possible when situations such as this arise.

We remain committed to the safety of our players and staff and will continue to monitor future situations. post_text:
The Center for Disease Control is now recommending all persons wear a cloth face covering to slow the spread of the coronoavirus and to keep people who may have the virus and do not know if from transmitting it to others. They have found a significant number of people who have the virus, do not have symptoms--but they can still transmit the virus to others. This means the virus can spread between people interacting in close proximity--for example, speaking, coughing, or sneezing--even if those people are not exhibiting symptoms. The cloth face coverings recommended are not surgical or medical grade masks. Those are critical supplies that must continue to be reserved for healthcare workers and other medical first responders. Just wear a simple cloth cover over your nose and mouth when in public--it can be homemade, it can be homemade, it can be a bandana, it can be anything you want it to be--JUST DO IT!!!
Thank you, Ingleside ISD

The San Patricio County Judge has passed an executive order of a "Stay Home Work Safe Measure" This executive order will begin at Midnight on March 30th.

This order will not affect the delivery of our education and Ingleside ISD will continue offering our Drive by lunches at the Primary school from 11 A.M. till 1 P.M.

Please Stay Home and stay safe so we can get back to normal and keep checking our website and our Facebook page for updates as we will continue to update them

Troy Mircovich, Superintendent, Ingleside ISD
